wikipedia_page.main: Antony John James (born 5 November 1989) is an English competitive swimmer who has represented Great Britain in the Olympics, FINA world championships and European championships, and England in the Commonwealth Games.  At the 2012 Summer Olympics in London, he competed in the men's 100-metre butterfly. Alongside swimming he has completed a Bsc (Hons) in Psychology at Plymouth University.
